The paper deals with the challenge of bias and confounding effects in machine learning applications, which is a common problem in several sub-fields of computer science. The proposed method is based on deep learning and adversarial training, which are techniques commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
